movie_name: Summer of Soul (...Or, When the Revolution Could Not Be Televised)
short_description: Documentary about the legendary 1969 Harlem Cultural Festival which celebrated African-American music and culture and promoted Black pride and unity.

facts_and_links: {'Trivia': ['The first moon landing took place during the festival. Interestingly, attendees of the festival who were interviewed about this momentous event had a different take about it - that it was a waste of money, seeing as there was so much poverty in the world. Harlem was dealing with a massive heroin epidemic at the time.', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7378922/trivia/?ref_=tt_dyk_trv'], 'Goofs': ['The subtitle, "When the Revolution Could Not Be Televised," is incorrect. In 1969, the year the Harlem Cultural Festival concerts took place, two TV specials about them were shown: Harlem Festival (1969) on July 28, 1969 on CBS (while the concerts were still taking place) and The Folk Gospel Music Festival (1969)on September 16, 1969 on ABC.', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7378922/goofs/?tab=gf&ref_=tt_dyk_gf'], 'Quotes': ["Sly Stone: Don't wait for approval from your neighbor, because your neighbor might be waiting for you.", 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7378922/quotes/?ref_=tt_dyk_qu'], 'Crazy credits': ['There is a scene after the end credits featuring Stevie Wonder and his band leader bantering back and forth on stage.', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7378922/crazycredits/?tab=cz&ref_=tt_dyk_cc'], 'Connections': ['Edited from Harlem Festival (1969)', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7378922/movieconnections/?ref_=tt_dyk_cnn'], 'Soundtracks': ['Drum SoloWritten by Stevie WonderPerformed by Stevie WonderPublished by Jobete Music Co.
